This is a fun debate by way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Anyway, loony Islamic Iraq, ok, you know much about Islam? Sunni (moderate), Shiite (extremist), ok that's very simplistic but a rough idea of the two main factions.<br>
  Saddam  and his allies are Sunni and secular, Iran backs a lot of the Shiites who live in the South East, Iran was wanting to help the Shiites during last Gulf War. Shiites are not literally extremists but tend to be, while Sunni's tend to preffer secular government. Many Muslims arent extremists but, the problem is the extremists ARE extreme, and use physical or clerical threats to garner support.<br>
  Currently Iran is having major convulsions with moderate and extremists, be nice ot see it go moderate as it seems many folk are sick fed up with the extremist crap, however the hard liners are brutal in their crack downs.<br>
  Saudi Arabia and other moderate countries, some suffering from very unjust/blockhead governments, have extremist problems, often because the governments policies has prevented the massive wealth getting to the ordinary people. making them hot beds of discontent. Action in Iraq bolsters the extremists' support.<br>
  American actions in the MiddleEast have generally been appallingy naive and gone awry. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elladin>Elladin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(2/18/03 5:03:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=364.topic&index=98>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: idiot socialists</span><hr size=1> Silver, the ruling party in Iraq has nothing to do with Islam or muslims. Saddam is NOT a muslim. He is a member of the Baath Party. The Baath Party is a political party which has been formed from a very old society - in fact, in older (way older, like thousands of years) times they were considered a society of assassins. Do you think Saddam cares anything for religion, muslim or otherwise? He gives a show of praying because it pleases the masses, but that is it.<br>
<br>
...and do you think that Americans are the only ones to make bad policy decisions in the middle east? Do you think everything that is wrong over there todays is America's fault? That is truly naive. Yes, I will agree with you that all of America's action / policies in the middle have not been the smartest, but other mistakes have been made as well by governments around the world and have been &quot;appallingly naive and have gone awry.&quot; <br>
<br>
Update here, I found this info on the web....<br>
<br>
&quot;&quot;Baath Party, formally the Baath Arab Socialist Party. political party and movement influential among Arab communities in the Middle East, especially in Syria and Iraq. The Baath Party was from the beginning a secular Arab nationalist party. Socialism (not Marxism) was quickly adopted as the party’s economic dogma... <br>
<br>
...In February 1963 the Baath Party came to power in Iraq and one month later, in March 8, it came to power in Syria after the March Revolution.&quot;&quot;<br>
<br>
As a matter of fact, Brittain has played a far larger role in the conditions you see in Iraq and its policies today... Brittain used to occupy Iraq.<br>
<br>
And last, just because the US and others have made mistakes in the middle east (many bad decisions were made during the years of the cold war as well), is that a reason to do nothing now? Yea, this one one of those pay me now, or pay me later types of deals. If we do nothing now, we will surely have to later.<br>
